episodes.name: Reconnecting in Retirement in Dominical, Costa Rica
episodes.overview: After years of running businesses from their farm, Canadians Doug and Jules are planning ahead for their retirement in sultry and slower paced Dominical, Costa Rica. But with their retirement savings on the line, their move to paradise hinges on striking the balance between her emotional and his financial divide when House Hunters International casts its net to Dominical, Costa Rica.

episodes.name: When Ajman loves a Woman
episodes.overview: Tired of living with regrets over not seeing the rest of the world, Maisha is leaving her life in Brooklyn behind to move to the United Arab Emirates. Maisha has been living a rich and full life in Brooklyn, NY with more friends than a girl could ask for and an active social life, but after she was not accepted into a graduate program, she made a bet with herself. If she applied to an international job and got it, she'd get on the plane and go. Now that she's received a job offer in Ajman, Maisha is on her way to a new life in the United Arab Emirates. Find out if this girl with a passion for the night life can adjust to a more conservative lifestyle in the Middle East as House Hunters International caravans into the United Arab Emirates.

episodes.name: Beautiful Backdrop in Tamarindo, Costa Rica
episodes.overview: When photographer Katie was shooting a wedding in Tamarindo, she not only fell in love with the idyllic beach town, but she also met her future boyfriend, Jeff. A year later, she felt divided between working at a flower shop in Aspen and pursuing her dream job. She knew it was time to make the leap and relocate to Costa Rica. While she starts up her business, she wants to stay close to town, but Jeff dreams of the surf. Find out if finding a budget friendly solution will add even more to Katie's fiscal concerns when House Hunters International catches a wave in Tamarindo, Costa Rica.

episodes.name: A Family of Five Strives to Find a Full-Size House in Cambridge, England
episodes.overview: For Carla and Andrew Nickodemus, Traverse City, which is Michigan's natural beauty and close knit community, made it an ideal place to raise their three kids, Brennan, Cassidy and Gavin. But when Carla was suddenly offered a job promotion in Cambridge, England, the family was thrown for a loop. Realizing it was a great opportunity to expose their children to a different culture, the Nickodemus family decided to embark on the adventure of a lifetime. But once they arrive on UK soil, they quickly learn traditional British homes lack the big American features they've grown accustomed to. Mom and Dad worry about the children's well being and about going over budget to get the size and central location they want. Find out if they can locate a comfortable property that fits their family of five when House Hunters International charters a course to Cambridge, England.

episodes.name: Quality Time in Bern, Switzerland
episodes.overview: Jeff's constant commuting between New Jersey and Chicago was putting a damper on the quality time he had to spend with his family. So when he was offered a unique work opportunity that would allow him to spend more time at home, he and his wife Emily knew he had to take it. The catch was that they would have to move to Bern, Switzerland. It will be a major culture shock for the kids, but they are up for it. Watch as real estate agent Barbara helps them keep it all in the family when House Hunters International travels to Bern, Switzerland.

episodes.name: Risky Beach Business in Leon
episodes.overview: The Hastings family already attempted to buy a house in Leon, Nicaragua. For risk analyst Jeff, though, the numbers didn't add up. So he brought his wife Natalie and two sons back home to Cincinnati to clear the deck and start researching all over again. Now, armed with the proper data and pushed along by his enthusiastic family, Jeff has returned one last time to Leon.

episodes.name: Living Life in La Baule
episodes.overview: When Randy Lawrence's company offered him a chance to work in France, wife Rebekah leapt at the opportunity to immerse her young daughters in the country's rich history. While Randy wants a modern home to ease the transition for their children, Rebekah craves a traditional property with a French feel. Now they'll have to choose between contemporary or traditional when House Hunters International experiences la vie in La Baule, France.

episodes.name: Searching for Keys in Cabo, Mexico
episodes.overview: Paris and Antonio are leaving the rolling vineyards of Napa Valley, California to find their dream home in Cabo San Lucas, Mexico. But the problem has been that until now, they're all look and no buy. They've toured over 200 homes already, and even lost a deposit once before. Paris is fearful on settling, worried that just after she buys a home, a better one will crop up. Antonio, on the other hand, is afraid that the search will go on forever. He's sick of being a visitor and wants to be a resident. It's high time for this couple to find a home that works for both of them, and the sooner the better.

episodes.name: Seeking Common Ground in Frankfurt, Germany
episodes.overview: When Chris Nealon's global auto company transferred him to Frankfurt, his wife, Katie, put her own beloved career as a speech language pathologist in limbo. With her future uncertain, she's anxious to find a space she can feel at home in. While Katie adores traditional detail and period features, Chris is all about clean lines and modern decor. With diametrically opposed preferences, this strong-willed young couple must find a way to compromise. House Hunters International learns that a house divided cannot stand in Frankfurt, Germany.

episodes.name: Seeking a Gem on the Caribbean Island of St. Maarten
episodes.overview: As a trained gemologist, Hilary Grant has learned to hone her eye to spot even the tiniest of flaws. This ability has opened the door for her to be recruited from California to apply her skills at a jewelry store in the Caribbean. Unfortunately for her husband Shawn, this attention to detail is not something she can easily turn off and on. Hilary is not shy about wanting the finest things in life and is willing to stretch their $2,900 a month budget to land the perfect place close to work. Shawn is not as flexible on budget, but as long as he has a space for a home office, he won't sweat the small stuff. But as they are both about to learn, any property in St. Maarten's expensive rental market comes with concessions. Watch as paradise is put under the microscope when House Hunters International visits the Dutch country of St. Maarten.

episodes.name: Pre-empting an Empty Nest on Nevis
episodes.overview: The Horners want a home on the remote Caribbean island of Nevis to enjoy their retirement together once their teenage children leave their Florida nest. But 18 years of savings isn't enough, so they must purchase a property they can successfully rent out until their retirement. Shay's long term goal to invite her future grandkids to visit challenges Steve's practical short term need for a rental. Find out if they can agree on a house or a condo, when House Hunters International retires to Nevis.

episodes.name: Business and Budget in Budapest, Hungary
episodes.overview: Drew and William moved to the tiny town of Saluda, North Carolina to take a step back from the rat race. Now they are ready to jump back in, and this time in the historic city of Budapest, Hungary. They like to put their own stamp on their homes, but after a lengthy experience renovating their home in Saluda, they said never again. Given William's background in architecture, a renovation project will be tough for them to resist. Drew's business is expanding into Europe, so their new home will need room for him to work as well. Robert Weiner will have his work cut out for him when he attempts to help this couple find their perfect home when House Hunters International goes to Budapest, Hungary.

episodes.name: New Digs in Dortmund, Germany
episodes.overview: Before Lauren and Oliver's whirlwind romance began, they each fell in love with expat life in Berlin. Now their once bohemian haven has become a hot spot and now they find themselves priced out of the city they've adopted as their own. So when a new job in more affordable Dortmund came up, Oliver knew they had to make the move. While Lauren wants a yard and suburban savings, he wants a city lifestyle at any cost. Real estate agent Janina will have a difficult time reconciling her clients' differing priorities as they figure out what's most important. Watch, When House Hunters International says guten tag to Dortmund, Germany.

episodes.name: Living la Vida Local in Puerto Cayo, Ecuador
episodes.overview: Steve and Dana have grown tired of their small town in Arkansas and decide to take off on an adventure into the unknown in Puerto Cayo, Ecuador. Steve's profession as a writer puts them in a perfect place to report back to other Americans on assimilating into the culture, but in order to get the full experience, they will have to look outside typical expat gated communities. With limited local options available, they find themselves looking at older construction, and they're starting to realize that some of the native Ecuadorian accommodations aren't exactly meeting their American needs.

episodes.name: Great Expectations, Low Budget in London, England
episodes.overview: When Danielle's boyfriend Jared mentioned he'd be willing to move to London, she jumped at the chance to make her dream of living abroad come true. But when this independent fashion designer's shrewdly high standards clash with her boyfriend's wants and the limitations of London's pricey and fast paced housing market, agent Toby Brown scrambles to meet her great expectations within their low budget, as House Hunters International demands perfection in London, England.

episodes.name: A Second Chance in The Netherlands Capital of Amsterdam
episodes.overview: A new job in Amsterdam has Californians Robert and Mary Jo Sandholm ready for a fresh start. After a bike accident forced Robert to stop working for seven years, Mary Jo stepped up and became the sole breadwinner for their family of six. Now that Robert's ready to return to the workforce as a Europe based marketing director for his company, he's excited to repay Mary Jo for helping him get back on his feet. She not only gets to return to the stay at home mom role she wants to fill, but Mary Jo also has the chance to recreate her childhood in the process. Growing up in the Irish countryside, she had an idyllic upbringing and she would love nothing more than for her family to have a similar experience in the Netherlands.

episodes.name: Size Matters to Husbands in Dublin
episodes.overview: Eli Hale leapt at the chance to transfer to Ireland when his husband Marcio Noia's work visa expired. But they're discovering very different opinions on the size of living space they desire. Marcio wants a large house to spread out in, but Eli thinks an apartment is a better fit. Now they'll have to find a compromise when House Hunters International takes a swig in Dublin, Ireland.

episodes.name: Opposites Attract in Oliva, Spain
episodes.overview: Victoria likes to keep busy, and Paul likes to lay back. When the couple decides to unwind with a vacation home on the coast of Spain, they learn it's not all siestas and sea views. With these opposite personalities, there's going to be a compromise. Watch as House Hunters International dials it back in Oliva Spain.

episodes.name: A Free-Spirited Couple Parks Their Mobile Home in Florida and Heads South to the Jungle in Belize
episodes.overview: It takes a special kind of bond to build a happy home, and an even more complex partnership to, well, live in a school bus you built together. As happy as their homemade mobile home is, artists Nikki and Ben are ready for an even bigger adventure. They're ready for the jungle. They're ready to move their relationship, and their careers, but not their bus, to the jungles of Belize, guided by only one mantra, the wilder the better. So with a well-heeled sense of adventure and a semi-vetted plan, Nikki and Ben park their bus-home and head south to the unknown. They may be up for anything, watch how far they can stretch a starving artist's salary in paradise when House Hunters International goes to San Ignacio, Belize.

episodes.name: Buenos Dias Barcelona, Spain
episodes.overview: After a visit to Spain left her enchanted, Raphaella decided to leave behind the daily grind in London to teach yoga in Barcelona. She wants a flat near the beach with enough outdoor space for a yoga class, but her friend Alasdair knows he'll have a hard time keeping her focused on her budget. Watch when House Hunters International breathes deep in Barcelona, Spain.

episodes.name: Belfast and Furious
episodes.overview: When Sarah encouraged her husband Dave to apply for post-doctoral studies all over the world, she never dreamed the first place he'd be accepted would be in Belfast Northern Ireland. Dave has already left Sarah behind in Michigan to start work and now she's putting her own education and teaching career on hold to join him in Belfast. Sarah will be looking for all the comforts of home, while Dave is more concerned with living close to his work. They'll also have the added stress of finding a suitable home for their dog Toby, who is accompanying them on their journey abroad. Find out if everyone can get what they want or if moving to a new country is just the start of Sarah's sacrifice as House Hunters International visits Belfast, Northern Ireland.

episodes.name: Long Distance Lovers Look for a Love Nest in Provence, France
episodes.overview: After two and a half years, Cheryse, an interior design student in Florida, and her boyfriend Sebastien, a chef in Massachusetts, are done with long distance dating. So, they make a move, get engaged, and relocate to his native France. Although life in Provence should be slower paced than the U.S., the couple soon find themselves overwhelmed with finding a place to live and planning their wedding. And, to top it off, Sebastien is in the midst of launching a food truck business with his brother. As the couple searches for a starter home, they struggle to find a flat with secure parking for his truck and that's similar in size to American homes. Find out if the challenge brings them together or tears them apart when House Hunters International gets hitched in Provence, France.

episodes.name: Fitting into Osaka, Japan
episodes.overview: With an eye on working less overtime, Russ accepts a job that takes him, his wife Erin, and their two boys to Osaka. However, coming from a 6,000 square foot home in Utah might not be the easiest transition to Japan's notoriously tiny living spaces. Russ wants to keep the family close together, but for Erin it might be a little too close for comfort. Watch as House Hunters squeezes into Osaka, Japan.

episodes.name: Too Cold for Comfort in Lulea, Sweden
episodes.overview: The Phillips family is leaving the security of their perfect life and big house in Utah to move to a small town in Sweden near the Arctic Circle. Eric will realize his dream of working internationally, while his wife Gini will have to quit her job and become a stay at home mom. Along with their one year old baby, they'll have to adjust their new lifestyle near the Arctic Circle, with its long, dark winters.

episodes.name: An Upwardly Mobile Athenian Moves In With a Roomie She's Never Met So She Can Find a Flat Fast
episodes.overview: Veronika loves her life in Athens, but there's a problem. Greece is in the throes of a prolonged economic crisis, and it's no place for a young woman to start a career. So when a promising opportunity emerges in Cyprus, Veronika decides to take a chance on this once-Greek isle, even though she doesn't know a single person there. With only two weeks 'til her first day, Veronika agrees to live with Irina, roommate she's never met. They may have friends in common, but with vastly different priorities, these blind date roommates will need to put in overtime to find some common ground.

episodes.name: Old or New in England's Surrey County
episodes.overview: For history buff Derek Smith, his job transfer from Houston, Texas to England's Surrey County is a dream come true. With its pastoral setting mixed with buildings standing from the time of the Tudors, Surrey County has all the old British charm that he could ever ask for. His wife Libby, however, is not interested in living in the past. She is giving up her job at NASA and is looking to her future by enrolling in design school. Libby gravitates to a modern aesthetic, not only in her design style but also in the type of home she wants to live. Finding middle ground on character is already going to be a challenge, but with rental homes in Surrey County here and gone in the blink of an eye, time is not on their side to endlessly debate old or new. Watch as Derek and Libby try to come to a decision before all their choices are history when House Hunters International takes a trip through the past, present, and future of England's Surrey County.

episodes.name: Teaching English to Finance an Endless Summer on Koh Samui, Thailand
episodes.overview: Katie and Jake have dated since high school and always wanted to travel the world together. After their wedding, they bought tickets and landed on Koh Samui, Thailand. Eager to stay, they took a Teaching English course, then found jobs at the International School in Lamai hoping to finance an endless summer. Now all they need to do is find the perfect place with a pool in paradise.

episodes.name: California Dreaming in Chioggia, Italy
episodes.overview: After 30 years of career and family life in California, Patty is moving back to Italy to care for her aging parents in her hometown of Chioggia. Patty's eager to reconnect with her roots, and though she faces limited rental options, she's uncompromising about her adopted American standards when House Hunters International angles for a balance in Chioggia, Italy.

episodes.name: Young Couple Butts Heads in Bruges
episodes.overview: Lana McCoy has always dreamed of living abroad. Her husband Chris wanted the American Dream. After a fateful test trip to Africa, Chris saw the light and took a job with an international company to make his wife's dream come true. But about a year into living in Serbia, Chris's company wants him to move to Belgium. Lana's leaping at the chance to explore, but Chris has reservations about starting over - again. He wants a rustic home close to work, and she wants modern living in the heart of Bruges. Now, they'll have to find a middle ground when House Hunters International seeks a sweet spot in Bruges, Belgium.

episodes.name: Domestic Track in Tasmania
episodes.overview: All work and no play, TV Exec Fiona thought she had it all. But after she and husband Craig started a family, she knew their pace of life had to change. So when he was offered a job in his native Tasmania, he knew there they could spend more time together as a family. But in this tiny property market, she's not sure if she's ready to compromise the rustic life she's dreamt of for his desire to live in a modern home. Watch when House Hunters International jumps feet first on the island state of Tasmania.

episodes.name: A History Teacher Encounters the Unknown in Ukraine
episodes.overview: Immediately after Maggie finished university in Canada, she took a teaching position in London, England. Enamored with Europe's rich history, she used the opportunity to soak in the sights. Two years later, eager to discover the East, she accepted a job in Kiev. Since Maggie's family left the Ukraine for Canada three generations ago, the thirty-year-old history buff was curious to learn more about her heritage. But, despite her background, Maggie doesn't speak the language and doesn't know a soul in the country's capital city. Faced with finding a flat in a foreign place, Maggie enlists her friend Michelle to help out. They hope two heads are better than one, but once the search starts they struggle to find a modern flat that's close to Maggie's downtown office on her modest budget of $900 a month. Find out if Maggie finds comfort in Kiev when House Hunters International takes a class on the Ukraine.

episodes.name: A Greece of the Action
episodes.overview: Concert pianist Julian has loved every minute of living a musician's life in New York City, having played in countless well known venues all across the world. Now that he and his wife Elektra have a new baby daughter, Nikita, Elektra has convinced Julian to move across the globe to Athens, Greece where she grew up, so the baby can be raised amongst her family. For the happiness of one baby, Julian will have to sacrifice his other baby, a 107-year-old grand piano that was his pride and joy ? until baby Nikita came along. With no way to move the piano to Greece, it will have to be left behind. It's up to Elektra and realtor Ellen to show Julian that life in Athens is every bit as good as life in Manhattan, but if Julian can't find a new piano, all bets are off. Find out if this turns out as just another Greek tragedy as House Hunters International visits Athens, Greece.

episodes.name: Urban Versus Rural in Kathmandu, Nepal
episodes.overview: Volunteer English teachers Kylie and Carly are moving in together to start teaching in Kathmandu, Nepal. The only catch is that they have never met. These two strangers not only have to navigate the Kathmandu rental market on a tight budget, they have to compromise on whether Carly will get what she wants in the center of town or if Kylie will get what she wants out in the country. Watch, as House Hunters International says Namaste to Kathmandu, Nepal.

episodes.name: A Compounding Conundrum in Papua New Guinea
episodes.overview: Just months after the first child was born, Andrew surprised Jackie with news that he'd gotten a new job in Lae, Papua New Guinea. For Jackie, giving up her family, friends and modern conveniences is a major sacrifice. Faced with a radically different culture and the instability of a developing nation, she's adamant about living in a well-secured expat compound. But, wary of the lacking privacy and noisy surroundings, Andrew's angling for a stand-alone house. Watch what happens when House Hunters International gets a taste of the local lifestyle in Lae, Papua New Guinea.

episodes.name: Haunted by a Hurricane on Grand Cayman Island
episodes.overview: Dax and Lily left Grand Cayman Island after Hurricane Ivan destroyed their home. A decade later, they want to return to the island of their dreams. Dax thinks the move should be permanent, but Lily worries about another big storm.

episodes.name: Fear of Pests in Brisbane
episodes.overview: Canadians Scott and Jennifer have decided to move to Brisbane, Australia, for Scott to attend medical school. While Scott is focused on school and living as close to campus as possible, Jennifer is hoping to live close to the city in an apartment above the ground floor where she won't have to worry about snakes, spiders and all things creepy-crawly invading her cozy home. She's also concerned about maintaining the couple's lifestyle on only her income. Can Scott convince his wife to embrace student-style living to save money, or will Jennifer stick closely to her list of requirements?

episodes.name: Raising a Family in Salzburg
episodes.overview: California couple Ashley and Mark recently welcomed their first child, Campbell. Shortly after the birth of their son, philosopher and professor Mark was awarded a prestigious fellowship, giving him the opportunity to work alongside other great minds in his field at a university in Austria. Now the young family of three is looking for a place to call home in Salzburg.

episodes.name: Sink or Swim in Bonaire
episodes.overview: Lifelong diving fanatics Kate and Ian must make a monumental decision between budget and location when searching for their dream home in Bonaire.

episodes.name: Beach Life Dream in Coronado
episodes.overview: John and Aisha are living out their lifelong dream by moving from the cold winters of Baltimore, Maryland, to the warm beach sands of Coronado, Panama. Aisha wants a house with a backyard for gardening, and John wants a condo directly on the beach.

episodes.name: Living Large in Languedoc
episodes.overview: Renee, a world-renowned photographer who specializes in nude photography, and her wife, Wendy, are leaving Los Angeles to establish their business in Europe. They are looking for a place to both work and live in the Languedoc region of France.

episodes.name: A New Life in Ireland
episodes.overview: College sweethearts Liam and Gillian are moving to Dublin, Ireland, to start a new life with their dog; Liam is excited to trace his grandfather's roots in Ireland, but their budget might be stretched thin by Gillian's extensive wish list.

episodes.name: A Return to Cambodia
episodes.overview: An Arizona couple looks for a home in Phnom Penh, Cambodia, where they first met. The stars have aligned for their return, but living space and an easy commute are a challenge in a city overwhelmed by new construction, noise and impossible traffic.

episodes.name: Culture Shock in Cambodia
episodes.overview: An Australian family gives up their modern lifestyle in Sydney to spend more time together in Sihanoukville, Cambodia. With limited disposable income and a simpler way of living, there are big sacrifices that need to be made in choosing a house.

episodes.name: Bebe in Guanacaste, Costa Rica
episodes.overview: A couple leaves small town Oregon for the beautiful beaches of Guanacaste, Costa Rica, to open a bed and breakfast. They battle it out to determine want versus need for their fledgling business.

episodes.name: Cuckoo for Playas del Coco
episodes.overview: A couple downsizes by selling their 40-acre farm in order to live a simpler life in Playas del Coco, Costa Rica. While he wants to start over with a clean slate and a minimalist life, she isn't quite ready to leave everything behind.

episodes.name: Dreaming in Donegal
episodes.overview: A woman and her two dogs are trading in the San Diego city life for the rustic charm of Donegal, Ireland. After spending a few years selling off two businesses and her home to make the trip abroad, she hopes to find a home in the country where she can be surrounded by her biggest passion -- animals.

episodes.name: Ready to be Roommates in Hanoi, Vietnam
episodes.overview: An adventurous couple from Cape Town, South Africa, is moving to Hanoi, Vietnam, where they will live together for the first time. They want to teach English to fund their travels, but with only her job to support them, he's on edge about finances.

episodes.name: Escape to Quito
episodes.overview: Inspired by a friend he met on an Ecuadorian volunteer trip, a young California accountant decides to find a home in Quito, Ecuador. Motivated by the idea of living near the Andes Mountains, the Galapagos Islands and the myriad of adventures that await transplants to Ecuador, he's ready to break out of his corporate bubble but such a move may be difficult for the frenetic dreamer. He has a long list of things he'd like in a home, but some of them are wildly contradictory. His real estate agent is committed to getting him to focus and prioritize while diving headlong into a wild house hunt in the exciting South American metropolis.

episodes.name: New Chapter in Valencia, Spain
episodes.overview: A couple with a mutual love for travel and exploration has returned to his parent's California home after eight months on the road. They quickly realize, however, they weren't quite ready to restart their corporate jobs and stop exploring the world together. Inspired by their world travels, they've decided to become their own bosses and start their own travel business in Valencia, Spain.

episodes.name: The Leap to London
episodes.overview: After getting the opportunity to transfer jobs from Seattle to London, a man with dreams of living overseas and his surprised wife are excited to start a new adventure together. He hopes to find a budget-friendly home with a short commute to his job in Piccadilly Circus. She's sacrificing a lot, however, so she wants the whole London experience in exchange, including a flat with English charm and plenty of room for visitors.

episodes.name: California to Lisbon, Portugal
episodes.overview: A couple of former actors are ready to leave the sunny West Coast to live their "third life" in beautiful Lisbon, Portugal. With his career as a teacher and one of the pioneers of acting for animators taking him across Europe, Lisbon would be the perfect jumping-off point for their new life. She's leaving behind her career for this adventure, though, so she wants to dive right into all the Lisbon charm their modest budget can afford.

episodes.name: Fearing Finnish Winters in Jyvaskyla
episodes.overview: A woman accepts a job in Jyvaskyla, Finland, knowing nothing about the location other than it has notoriously cold and dark winters. Despite assurances from her friend and agent that winter is manageable, her fear runs wild and she finds herself tasked with choosing between spreading her finances too thin or embracing a winter commute.

episodes.name: Long-Term Living in Denmark
episodes.overview: A Pennsylvania couple goes all-in to pursue one's career in Copenhagen, Denmark. While Mike wants to embrace minimalism and local living, Derek feels he has given up a lot and wants to be comfortable in his home.

episodes.name: Swapping Cities Inside Vietnam
episodes.overview: A young couple moves from Hanoi to Ho Chi Minh City, Vietnam, ready to take the next step in their relationship. They're all-in on the move, but leaving their comfort zone and choosing where to live in the new, glamorous city launches an unexpected battle of wills.

episodes.name: Mother Knows Best in Cape Town
episodes.overview: After spending years on sabbatical in busy India, an ex-Buddhist monk follows her daughter's career to Cape Town, South Africa. While the area has something to offer for both of them, their dueling priorities threaten to upset the peace.

episodes.name: Designing a Dream Car in Turin
episodes.overview: A man follows his passion for automotive design to go study in Turin, Italy. He's looking for a stylish apartment that's close to school, but having space to accommodate visitors while staying in his budget will be a challenge.

episodes.name: Heigh-Ho Lo de Marcos
episodes.overview: These empty nesters made a lot improvements to their Colorado rental hoping to purchase, but when the housing market skyrocketed, they had to come up with plan B. The affordability and status of Lo de Marcos made it an easy choice on where to buy.

episodes.name: Copenhagen, You've Changed
episodes.overview: Time in Copenhagen impressed this Atlanta man when he was a young intern. Thirteen years later, he's returned to live the Danish dream, but with a new husband in tow and an ever-tightening real estate market, he might be in for a rude awakening.

episodes.name: Operation Baby Bundle in Sicily
episodes.overview: An expecting American couple is moving to Sicily due to his deployment and must find a home on a budget. He wants a one-bedroom apartment on the water and close to town, while she prefers a three-bedroom apartment with access to outdoor space for their dog. With a baby on the way, she is prioritizing practicality, while he is eyeing an easy path to the beach.

episodes.name: Adventure and Expectations in Bangkok
episodes.overview: A husband looking to live abroad moves his family from Denver to Bangkok. He and the kids are looking for adventure. But Mom is having trouble adapting to the different pace, and managing her expectations of a suburban home may be challenging.

episodes.name: Mixing Cultures in Morocco
episodes.overview: A Canadian couple relocates to Tangiers, Morocco, and is excited to embrace the culture -- to a certain extent. He favors a traditional Moroccan-style space in keeping with their move, but she prefers the more familiar comforts of home, including a modern, spacious kitchen.

episodes.name: Teachers Learn the Strange Ways of Taipei
episodes.overview: A young couple takes a chance in Taipei, Taiwan after mutual job opportunities arise. They have a friend in town, but even with help, agreeing on what area to live in is a challenge in this land of heavy traffic, odd restaurants and stinky tofu.

episodes.name: A Fresh Start in Singapore
episodes.overview: An Australian woman convinced her husband to take a job in Singapore. It was her idea to move, so he's hoping to get the resort-style apartment of his dreams. But in one of the world's most expensive cities, they may be getting in over their heads.

episodes.name: A Francophile in Montreal

episodes.name: Teaching and Learning in Madrid
episodes.overview: A husband-and-wife teaching duo relocates from Malaysia to Madrid, Spain. They're eager to teach in an entirely new cultural environment, but they quickly learn that the differences between Malaysia and Madrid extend all the way to the housing market.

episodes.name: Designing a New Life in Logan, Australia
episodes.overview: Newly married, a designer from Cincinnati is joining her paramedic husband in Australia so that he can go to medical school. He's busy with school and work, but she's has time on her hands and is eager to put her design skills to work, whatever the cost.

episodes.name: French Rivera, Family-Style
episodes.overview: A family barely unpacks in Germany when opportunity strikes on the extravagant French Riviera. They're expecting a new baby at any time, so the pressure is on to quickly find a family home in one of the most expensive places on the planet.

episodes.name: Back to Basics in Xalapa
episodes.overview: When the demands of a banking career become too much, a Chicago businesswoman decides to relocate to Xalapa, Mexico. She's eager to embrace her Mexican heritage and start a holistic business, but with limited resources, switching gears might not be easy.

episodes.name: Newfound Freedom in Brisbane
episodes.overview: An empty nester scientist stumbles into a job offer abroad in Brisbane, Australia. His wife has high expectations for their newfound freedom and wants to splurge on the city life, but he's gripping his wallet just as tightly as he did back home.

episodes.name: A New Scene in the Whitsundays
episodes.overview: A successful showbiz couple agrees it’s time to slow their pace and move to the Whitsunday Islands in Australia. Going back to her home turf seems like the perfect compromise, but it remains an open question just how country a city girl can go.

episodes.name: Bangkok Family Adventure
episodes.overview: A family leaves behind their idyllic life in Florida for a job opportunity in Bangkok. Mom has lived internationally before and looks to share the adventure with their kids, and they're quickly discovering that finding a home is part of the fun.

episodes.name: Arnhem Under the Microscope
episodes.overview: A microbiologist has the opportunity do his postdoctoral work in Arnhem, Netherlands, but his wife has never lived more than 30 minutes from her tiny hometown. With so much change unfolding, it's their house hunt that's under the microscope.

episodes.name: A Dutch Homecoming
episodes.overview: After years in New York, a woman is returning return home to Amsterdam to introduce her kids with their Dutch heritage, but her American husband can't shake his high standards and need for the familiar while they rush to find work and a new home.

episodes.name: Family in Focus in Alicante, Spain
episodes.overview: After years of working around the clock, an Orlando family seizes the opportunity to try a slower, more family-oriented lifestyle in Alicante, Spain. They've quit their jobs, sold their house, packed a few suitcases and ready to see what awaits.

episodes.name: Mixing Business With Pleasure in Playa del Carmen
episodes.overview: A couple hopes to leave the stress of Los Angeles and start a real estate business in Playa del Carmen, Mexico. One wants to live the dream with a pricey private getaway, while his husband pushes for a practical option so they can focus on their business.

episodes.name: From Sun to Rain in the London Suburbs
episodes.overview: An Arizona family is excited to shake things up with a work move to expensive London. The suburbs offer more bang for their buck in a booming market, but the winds of change have mom and dad wanting different things in a place where nothing comes cheap.

episodes.name: Living It Up in Puerto Aventuras
episodes.overview: A couple and their five kids move from Nashville to family-friendly Puerto Aventuras, Mexico. When health issues arose for him, it was the final push they needed to make some changes, slow down and put the focus back on family time.

episodes.name: Worry and Wine in New Zealand
episodes.overview: A dream-chasing couple relocates to work in the blooming wine industry in Marlborough, New Zealand. One has to work in a faraway town, and so they're forced to decide whether Marlborough is an everyday home for one, or a weekend retreat for two.

episodes.name: Worlds Collide in Wide Bay
episodes.overview: After a decade abroad, a woman returns to her hometown to open a cafe in the Wide Bay region of Australia. Her husband hopes to enjoy life by the beach, but she wants the convenience of being close to her mom's house for help with their two young kids.

episodes.name: Saddle Up in the Sunshine Coast
episodes.overview: Along with their horse, a family of six looks to relocate from Singapore to Australia. A multimillion-dollar budget helps, but when mom and dad disagree on location, all the money (and hay) in the world might not be enough to get them what they want.

episodes.name: Welcome to the Jungles of Costa Rica
episodes.overview: An adventurous couple is buying their future home in Costa Rica. He wants to relive his childhood with a funky forest treehouse, while she's in search of a sensible, modern home with accessible roads, a pool and room for their six kids.

episodes.name: Caution in Costa Rica
episodes.overview: Two Utah newlyweds are setting up shop in a remote Costa Rican city with a plan to start a yoga retreat together. She's ready to go all-in on a space that delivers from day one, but he insists on playing it safe as they get their business off the ground.

episodes.name: Mexico City Remix
episodes.overview: A young couple feels their house is owning them in New York and decides to relocate to Mexico City. They're looking for a lower cost of living and professional flexibility, but with one income to start, they need a place that's super cheap.

episodes.overview: A New Yorker fell in love on a business trip to Mexico, and now they're closing the distance with a home in Mexico City. It might be his hometown, but she's opinionated about the neighborhood, the fashion and just about everything else.

episodes.overview: When her boyfriend is offered a job in Melbourne that he can't refuse, a New Yorker nervously trades her beloved hometown for his native Australia. She wants a lively neighborhood, but having only one income leaves them with limited options.

episodes.overview: A fitness entrepreneur and his showbiz wife are leaving their hectic LA lives to pursue a business venture in Tulum, Mexico. She wants to start slow with a modern house in town, but he prefers to hit the ground running with a home in the jungle.

episodes.overview: A New Zealand man is giving up life as a professional cricket player and moving to Rotterdam, Netherlands. He's looking forward to starting a career in business and buying his first home, but in a competitive market, he may have to temper expectations.

episodes.name: From Hectic to Home on the Sunshine Coast, Australia

episodes.overview: A couple is finally realizing their plan to adopt a more chill lifestyle in Cabo San Lucas, Mexico. He’s the life of the party and wants to live downtown near the action, but she's a homebody who prefers a little distance from the ruckus to relax.

episodes.name: Leaving New York for Love Down Under

episodes.name: Empty Nest and Wallet in Los Cabos
episodes.overview: San Diego empty nesters are looking forward to their next phase in Mexico. She wants luxurious amenities and space for the kids to visit, no matter the cost. He's taking a more conservative approach with the dollars and cents. The search is upended when she falls in love with a resort-style condo with Mexican flair and a big price tag.

episodes.overview: After living apart for years, best friends decide to forge a new life in Glasgow, Scotland. They're looking for love and a chance to enjoy the city's nightlife, but finding a home that suits them both may test the limits of their friendship and finances.

episodes.name: Soccer or Sea Views in Christchurch, New Zealand
episodes.overview: A mother and son move for his young career in professional soccer to Christchurch, New Zealand. He's looking for a place where they can take in the sea views, but he doesn't drive, so she wants to stay practical with a home close to soccer practice.

episodes.name: Stepping Into Uncharted Territory in Madrid
episodes.overview: After exploring 35 countries in search of a permanent home, a digital nomad looks to finally set some roots in Madrid. Although she's a seasoned world traveler, she may be in for a surprise or two, because this is one city that she's never even been to.

episodes.name: Family of Vets Reset in Beaconsfield, England
episodes.overview: Veterinary surgeons give up their custom home and veterinary hospital for more family time in Beaconsfield, England. They dream of walking their kids to school in a small English town, but their adjustment from luxurious Texas spaces may be a challenge.

episodes.name: Family First in Christchurch, New Zealand
episodes.overview: A family in California looks to leave their San Francisco life behind to pursue a better balance of work, play and family time in Christchurch, New Zealand.

episodes.name: Buying a Puerto Vallarta Paradise
episodes.overview: After years of vacationing in Mexico, a couple now looks to buy a home in Puerto Vallarta to avoid harsh Canadian winters. With a surging market and an extensive wish list, however, they may have waited too long to find the good deal they were hoping for.

episodes.name: London Nanny Seeks Solitude on Vanuatu
episodes.overview: After years of nannying for wealthy families, an Australian woman looks to use her life savings to buy a beachfront home on Vanuatu. She's looking for peace and serenity in this island paradise, but adjusting to off-the-grid living may be a challenge.

episodes.name: A Serendipitous Journey from Atlanta to Valencia
episodes.overview: After falling for its charm, a family decides to move from Atlanta to Valencia, Spain. They look to transition to Spanish life and remote work, but now, they must weigh the cultural allure of city living against what that will cost.

episodes.name: Hitting the Pause Button in Brasilito
episodes.overview: A Virginia mother wants her daughter to experience a slower pace of life in Brasilito, Costa Rica. She's looking to escape a frantic, consumer-driven culture, but she may experience some unexpected sticker shock.

episodes.name: Ready vs. Reluctant in Espiritu Santo, Vanuatu
episodes.overview: A Cairns couple wants to be closer to nature and relocates to the developing island of Espiritu Santo, Vanuatu. He plans to use the archipelago as a backdrop for his nature videos, but the lack of western amenities has her rethinking the move entirely.

episodes.name: Family Seeks Multigenerational Home in Costa Rica
episodes.overview: A father-daughter team searches for a million-dollar multigenerational home on the jungle coast of Brasilito, Costa Rica. They have an extensive wish list, and an ocean view, a pool and separate guest quarters are all required.

episodes.name: Singing in the City, in Stockholm
episodes.overview: After a health scare, a husband and wife look to fulfill their dream of living abroad in Stockholm, Sweden. He seeks the vibrancy of the city center, but space is hard to come by in town, and she needs enough room to teach opera lessons from home.

episodes.name: NYC Woman Seeks Love in Amsterdam
episodes.overview: A NYC woman is leaving everything for one last shot at finding love and starting a family in Amsterdam. Not only is she searching for her dream man, she also wants the dream apartment, but with Amsterdam's housing crunch, those dreams may be in jeopardy.

episodes.name: Community Connection vs. Comfort in Tulum, Mexico
episodes.overview: A couple looks to escape their hectic Miami lives and slow down in Tulum, Mexico. He pictures a walker's paradise in the heart of the older downtown, but she wants a spacious and luxurious new build in the suburbs.

episodes.name: The Return of Ciao House, Puglia Edition
episodes.overview: When Food Network's "Ciao House" premiered last year, "House Hunters International" helped the show's celebrity chef find a Tuscan villa. Now in Season 2, the stakes are even higher as he hunts for a seaside farmhouse in Southern Italy.

episodes.name: Family Time in Valencia, Spain
episodes.overview: After their daughter's birth, a young couple leaves Florida for a better work-life balance in Valencia, Spain. He's hoping to replicate the space and luxury of their suburban home, but she's looking to enjoy city life and save money for traveling.

episodes.name: Adventurous Oregon Family Goes Dutch
episodes.overview: Charmed by an Amsterdam vacation, an adventurous Oregon family looks to relocate and go all-in on the Dutch way of life. Dad looks to experience life in the city, but mom wants the kind of spaciousness that's only found in the outskirts.

episodes.name: Recapturing the Excitement of Their Youth in La Drova, Spain
episodes.overview: After 30 years together, two ex-circus performers decide to shake up their quiet life and relocate to La Drova, Spain. He wants a secluded standalone house and doesn't mind reno projects, but she wants a traditional Spanish home that's move-in ready.

episodes.name: Ex-Army Brats in Bury St Edmunds
episodes.overview: A couple who met in high school in Germany reconnected 15 years later, married and blended their families. Now empty nesters, they're leaving their large Florida home behind to revisit European life together in Bury St Edmunds, England.

episodes.name: Mining for a House in Gympie, Australia
episodes.overview: After seven years and four children in Spain, a couple looks to move back to his homeland of Australia. He's starting a new career in the mining town of Gympie, but with just one income, striking gold won't be easy.

episodes.name: Riding the Winds of Change in Wellington
episodes.overview: After living in a small condo in Canada, a family chases a dream job in Wellington, New Zealand. They want a standalone house with a yard that's close to schools and work, but navigating the wind, terrain and a tight market may be a challenge.

episodes.name: He'll Fight Anything but a Bug in Pattaya, Thailand
episodes.overview: After falling in love with Thailand's rich tradition of combat sports, a Brazilian jiu-jitsu enthusiast looks to move to train, teach and chill in Pattaya. He has a healthy fear of bugs, so he'll have to fight to find a suitable apartment he can afford.

episodes.name: Newlyweds in Loughborough
episodes.overview: After a whirlwind romance in Texas, a newlywed couple relocates for his new job in Loughborough, England. She's giving up her career and hopes to start a family, and he wants to make her happy, but they're learning that they have different priorities.

episodes.name: Luxury Lifestyle for Less in Brisbane, Australia
episodes.overview: A desire to live abroad has a British family going down under with a move to Brisbane, Australia. They want a place with a pool and she's looking for modern luxuries in the city, but he's more concerned with keeping the costs down.

episodes.name: Single Mom Finds Her Calm in Siem Reap, Cambodia
episodes.overview: A single mom looks to leave the Los Angeles grind to fully immerse herself in Cambodian culture. She plans to move to a neighborhood where her dollars will stretch further, but her tween daughter prefers the posh expat lifestyle in central Siem Reap.

episodes.name: Feeling the Squeeze in Seoul, South Korea
episodes.overview: A recent college grad is moving out of her parents' house in Las Vegas to try life with her long distance boyfriend in Seoul, South Korea. She has a tiny budget, and with Seoul's micro-apartment scene, her big dreams may clash with an expensive reality.

episodes.name: Staking out Australia's Sunshine Coast
episodes.overview: Following her divorce, an English mom of two looks for a new life and a new career as a private investigator on Australia's Sunshine Coast. She wants a home that's by the beach, but finding a place that meets her high standards may be a challenge.

episodes.name: A Search for Comfort in Chambery, France
episodes.overview: A couple looks to honor his late brother by leaving Los Angeles and relocating their family closer relatives with a move to Chambery, France. He wants a place that's walkable in the city center, but she prefers a standalone house in a more quiet area.

episodes.name: Condesa vs. Room for Family in Mexico City
episodes.overview: A young woman leaves her hometown of Miami to focus on finishing her dissertation in Mexico City. She's looking for a home near the green spaces of Condesa, but her sister is along on the hunt to advocate for place with enough room to accommodate visits.

episodes.name: A Dream of Living Abroad That Almost Wasn't
episodes.overview: A breast cancer survivor looks to uproot her husband and two boys from California and move to Torquay, Australia. She wants to fulfill her dream of living abroad, but to ensure their big move is a success, he may need to put the brakes on their budget.

episodes.name: Shocked Southerners Adjust to Outrageous Amsterdam
episodes.overview: Proper Southern newlyweds look to relocate after his start-up company sends him abroad to Amsterdam. They're looking to purchase a spacious home with an outdoor space for their dog, but with limited inventory, their budget may not meet their expectations.

episodes.name: A Dog's Eye View of Life in London
episodes.overview: A globetrotting Texas couple and their beloved canine companion look to settle down in England. They have opposing financial views, and moving to pricey London is hard enough, but factoring in their dog's opinion could make things even more complicated.

episodes.name: Reno vs. Turnkey in Cork, Ireland
episodes.overview: Despite a massive housing crisis, a Seattle couple with a lifelong dream to move abroad relocates to Cork, Ireland. She's looking for a fixer-upper, but with his job starting right away, he wants something that's move-in ready.

episodes.name: Sacrificing Food for Family in Bavaria, Germany
episodes.overview: After five years in Cleveland, a young family looks to relocate to his homeland of Bavaria, Germany. They want to expose their young daughter to his German roots, but finding a spacious house that meets mom's high expectations may be a challenge.

episodes.name: A Family Mission in Chiang Rai, Thailand
episodes.overview: After building a nonprofit in Honduras, an adventurous couple moves their family to Chiang Rai, Thailand. They're looking to continue their global mission to help the less fortunate, but finding a home that meets both their wish lists may be a challenge.

episodes.name: Coming of Age in Madrid
episodes.overview: After falling in love with the city while she was in college, a young woman looks to return to earn her master's degree in Madrid. A fellow ex-pat is along to help find her first solo place ever, but scoring a home on a student budget may be a challenge.

episodes.name: 5000 Miles from Saskatoon to Costa Rica
episodes.overview: A couple upends their life in remote Saskatoon, Canada, by purchasing a restaurant in Dominical, Costa Rica. She wants to keep housing expenses low as they navigate their new occupation, but he wants air conditioning and a pool at any cost.

episodes.name: A Whale of an Adventure in Hervey Bay, Australia
episodes.overview: After leaving France for a post-college wilderness adventure, a young nature lover dives into adulthood in Hervey Bay, Australia. She's eager for her own independent space, but on her small budget, she quickly learns that housemates will be a necessity.

episodes.name: Leaving Work for Puerto Morelos, Mexico
episodes.overview: After living his entire life in Washington, a man decides to sell his business and start anew in Puerto Morelos, Mexico. He's looking for a house that's large enough for visiting family, but with limited inventory, he may need to consider a condo.

episodes.name: Setting Up a New Goal in Seville, Spain
episodes.overview: A Florida mother convinces her husband to embark on an adventure and relocate their family sight unseen to Seville, Spain. He hopes to ease their transition with a familiar family home, but she wants to go all in with a place that's traditionally Spanish.

episodes.name: Dreaming of Parisian Charm in the Latin Quarter
episodes.overview: A Bostonian designer quits her job to follow her dream of living in Paris. She's searching for French charm and space to work remotely, but finding a place in her budget that's in her favorite neighborhood, the Latin Quarter, may be a challenge.

episodes.name: A New Beginning in Kaiserslautern, Germany
episodes.overview: Former best friends reconnect and marry, and embark on their first international move together to Kaiserslautern, Germany. She's used to a nomadic lifestyle and wants German charm, but he prefers something modern with an easy commute to his new job.

episodes.name: Making Friends and Art in Mexico City
episodes.overview: A Detroit native with a remote job embraces her wanderlust and moves to Mexico City. She's looking for personal connections, artistic outlets and an apartment with good vibes, but finding the right space in her desired neighborhood may be out of reach.

episodes.name: New York Glamour to Wiesbaden Wonder
episodes.overview: A successful couple leaves New York to start a family in idyllic Wiesbaden, Germany. She's halting her stressful career and wants a luxurious lifestyle, but going down to one income has him keeping an eye on spending.

episodes.name: Mommy's Making It in Merida, Mexico
episodes.overview: A single mom decides that her teenage daughter is old enough to uproot from Jamaica to Merida, Mexico. She has big dreams of exploring a new culture and growing her travel vlog, but finding a place downtown that's in her budget may be a challenge.

episodes.name: From Brazil to the Redlands, Down Under
episodes.overview: A Brazilian family of four embarks on a new job opportunity and relocates to the Redlands, Australia. They're looking for a place that's walkable to shops and beaches, and she wants a modern apartment, but he prefers a large house with outdoor space.

episodes.name: Hunting for a House and a Husband in Hanoi
episodes.overview: A woman who has built her international teaching credentials in China looks to relocate to Hanoi, Vietnam. She's looking to gain more teaching experience and more of a personal life, but finding a place big enough to hold all her stuff may be a challenge.

episodes.name: A Move to Dad's Favorite Cambodian City, Phnom Penh
episodes.overview: A travel-loving New Zealand couple makes the most of an unexpected job loss with a family move to Phnom Penh, Cambodia. They're looking for something modern with two bedrooms that's near daycare, but their wish list may be too big for their budget.

episodes.name: Forget Paris, We're Buying in Bordeaux
episodes.overview: A married couple looks for a fresh start and a slower pace in Bordeaux, France. They're looking for something in the Bordeaux Hyper Centre and need separate office spaces, but finding a place in the city that's in their budget may be a challenge.

episodes.name: Dream Military Assignment in Pordenone, Italy
episodes.overview: After living in middle America for a decade, a New Mexico couple gets a dream military assignment in Pordenone, Italy. One is looking for something modern while the other wants Italian charm, and their differing visions for a home may present a challenge.
